"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-27-olympic-star-begs-fan-replace-mid-match-losing-eight-games-a-row-21309705\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Olympic tennis star Matthew Ebden begged a fan to replace him during his brutal first-round singles defeat toNovak DjokovicatParis2024 on Saturday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 147, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20, \"end\": 33, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Ebden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthew Ebden\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Ebden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Ebden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Australian simply could not handle Djokovic as the Serbian conjured up a brutal 6-0 bagel and then raced into a 2-0 second-set lead with an early break inside just 30 minutes at Roland-Garros, usually home to the iconicFrench Open.\", \"from\": 149, \"to\": 384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 149, \"end\": 163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8694826660984226e-14, \"text\": \"The Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\"}, {\"begin\": 204, \"end\": 211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.8113507688983397, \"rank\": 0.22579438857878897, \"text\": \"Serbian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After losing his eighth game of the match in a row, Ebden turned around and offered his racket to anyone in the crowd who would be willing to step in for him.\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 544, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It came after Ebden controversially attempted an underarm serve - seen as unsportsmanlike and frowned upon in tennis - as he still lost the point to Djokovic, with the 24-time Grand Slam champion eventually winning 6-0 6-1.\", \"from\": 546, \"to\": 769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 695, \"end\": 703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.194706514331892e-21, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking on the court after his dominant victory, Djokovic,who is projected to next face Big Three rival Rafael Nadalin an absolute blockbuster, turned to Ebden and simply said: 'Sorry man!'\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 961, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 821, \"end\": 829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.194706514331892e-21, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ebden threw his shirt over his head in an ironic celebration when he finally won his first game of the match late into the second set.\", \"from\": 963, \"to\": 1097, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Aussie is not best known for his skills in singles tennis but he is one of the best doubles players in the entire sport, currently ranked world No.3.\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1252, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Safe to say l'm officially retired from singles after that!'\", \"from\": 1254, \"to\": 1315, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ebden said.\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1327, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'It was a pleasure to share the court with you Novak for one last singles match on Philippe Chatrier here at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1411, \"end\": 1428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Chatrier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philippe Chatrier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Chatrier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Chatrier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'All the best for the rest of the tournament (and if it's not one of our Aussies) I hope you get the [gold medal].'\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1567, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ebden has won three Grand Slam titles - two in men's doubles and the other in mixed doubles - with his most recent triumph at the Australian Open this year.\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1725, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When it wasn't going Matthew Ebden's way so he asked if any fans wanted to take his place \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098#BBCOlympics#Olympics#Paris2024pic.twitter.com/wVd0vbkmpO  But he did not have enough to test Djokovic, who is desperate to land a gold medal for Serbia, in what is highly likely to be the last Games of his incredible career.\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 2045, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1748, \"end\": 1761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Ebden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthew Ebden\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Ebden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Ebden\"}, {\"begin\": 1914, \"end\": 1922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.194706514331892e-21, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 1966, \"end\": 1972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.99958006504452, \"rank\": 0.00042000224816222595, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Of course, the Olympics are a huge desire of mine, Djokovic said.\", \"from\": 2047, \"to\": 2113, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2099, \"end\": 2107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.194706514331892e-21, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'It's a unique opportunity, I have a bronze from Beijing 2008.'\", \"from\": 2114, \"to\": 2177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2163, \"end\": 2175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999433916871, \"rank\": 3.1420964508128476e-08, \"text\": \"Beijing 2008\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Djokovic hasfired a message to the trollswho'd 'love' him to enter retirement after the Olympic tennis tournament at Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2190, \"end\": 2198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.194706514331892e-21, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Novak Djokovic's possible path to landing a singles medal at the Paris Olympics:  'I do not have retirement close in my mind, to be honest,' Djokovic, 37, added.\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2320, \"end\": 2334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Novak Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 2461, \"end\": 2469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.194706514331892e-21, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Even though I know a lot of people would love me to retire so this era is done.\", \"from\": 2482, \"to\": 2562, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'But I think as long as there is at least one of us left competing, the era is still going.\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Of course there is a change of generations.\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2701, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You have Alcaraz and [Jannik] Sinner, currently they are our two best players in the world, deservedly\\u2026 But I have been present for the shift of many generations in the last 15 years.'\", \"from\": 2702, \"to\": 2886, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2711, \"end\": 2718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8519174829044873e-19, \"text\": \"Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:US cycling mechanic slips and goes flying in rain-drenched women's time trial at Paris Olympics  ArrowMORE:Tom Daley fans declare 'Olympics has started' as diver spotted knitting in crowd  ArrowMORE:Dutch Olympian who raped 12-year-old is not a paedophile, says senior official  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and mo